social_posts.post_text: Ditched the hair, I couldn’t take the poof anymore haha. Digging this though!
2022 was something. 2023 probably will be too.
I haven’t taken photos in almost a year so I edited some shots from back then. Feeling the itch again.
Hairline like Vegeta, body like Buu
Mud won’t be the only thing busting.
It would appear I have taken some photographs. Turn your brightness up I like my edits dark apparently.
“Wow, look at this rock” -me again, probably
Back in my comfort zone, urban and street photography scratches my brain infinitely more than landscapes.
Which one speaks to you the most? Why?
I don’t usually take photos of cars but this location was begging for it. Would have preferred a beautiful Italian model but this fat ole German works, too.

I walked around my hometown and tried some night photography. It is hard lol. 

Making a solid effort to shoot more in landscape this year instead of portrait solely for the gram.

Windows and doors. 

I said I was done with portrait but these just work better oriented this way lol
